@NODE "introduction" "Introduction"
@NEXT "legalstuff"
@PREV "Main"

@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

MagicClock is a analogous clock for the Workbench.
Everbody who's using MagicWB should also use MagicClock, because the look has
made in such a way that it fits to the MagicWB-look.
You certainly can change the look of MagicClock so that it appeals to you.
It does`nt matter, if you like e.g a one-color background, a colorpattern, a
brush (MWB) or a snaped windowbackground.
I tried to make the use of MagicClock as easy as possible but if there 
is something you don't understand, read the guidefile.
If there are still problems, you find a bug, you want to make some
suggestions or what ever, write or mail to one of the @{"addresses" link "authors"}.

I wish you a lot of fun with MagicClock  ;-)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "history" "History"

@{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}@{i}26.06.1995      V1.0 @{ub}@{ui}

- First Public Release

@{b}@{i}05.08.1995      V1.1 @{ub}@{ui}

- font adaptation rewritten
- About now runs correctly with Kickstart 2.x / better fonthandling
  (reported by Michael Taylor)
- problem while refreshing, while the secondhand is turned off, removed
  (reported by Chris Kerr)
- defaultpath is now set correctly at the end of the program
- error while snapping at the screenborder removed
- degrees corected to 0-359
- datatypes support added
- Pop To Back added
- Dithering added
- Snap/ Snap Always  now work with MagicLayers
- error with Color- and Sliderrequesters removed
- selectable ReMap
- Notify for Background added (for Snap Always)
- selectable picturescaling added

@{b}@{i}17.08.1995      V1.2 @{ub}@{ui}

- Dotmatix-Dithering added
- another bug while refreshing with no secondhand fixed
  (reported by Chris Kerr)
- used now AllocBitMap (V39+) and a special routine for lower versions
- >Open Prefs< fixed
- Fit To X,Y fixed (should not crash anyway)
  (reported by Frank Pagels)
@ENDNODE

