@NODE "display" "Display"

@{" Minute " link "nminute"}
@{" Hour   " link "nhour"}
@{" Quarter" link "nquarter"}
@{" Twelve " link "ntwelve"}

@{bg shine}Reversemode@{bg background}

The clock suddenly runs backwards.

@{bg shine}Fit Window To X
Fit Window To Y@{bg background}

The program tries to fit the opposide side to the selected so, that the
clock looks quadratic.
The program uses display informations from the system.
But it is possible that it does`nt look like a square. That could be because
of special monitorsettings.
To correct this take a look at the next 3 items.

@{bg shine}Use User Aspect@{bg background}

Switchs to user defined aspect.

@{bg shine}Set X-Aspect...@{bg background}

Sets the aspect for the x-direction.

@{bg shine}Set Y-Aspect...@{bg background}

Sets the aspect for the y-direction.

@{bg shine}Don't Pop@{bg background}

Turns >Pop To Front< respectively >Pop To Back< off.

@{bg shine}Pop To Front@{bg background}

That means the MagicClock-window is always in front of all other windows on
screen.

@{bg shine}Pop To Back@{bg background}

That means the MagicClock-window is always back of all other windows on
screen.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "nminute" "Minute"

Adjustments for the @{u}@{b}minute-element@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}On/Off@{bg background}

Turns the minute-element on/off.

@{bg shine}Open...@{bg background}

Loads a saved minute-element.

@{bg shine}Triangle@{bg background}

Sets the minute-element to the internal triangle-form.

@{bg shine}Point@{bg background}

Sets the minute-element to the internal point-form.

@{bg shine}Rectangle@{bg background}

Sets the minute-element to the internal rectangle-form.

@{bg shine}Transparent@{bg background}

Draws only the border of the minute-element.

@{bg shine}Unturned@{bg background}

The element will not be turned with the dail.
This mode isn't only very nice, its also an advantage, if your workbench
works with a low resolution, because it helps to reduce the contortion.
If you make your own element you have to notice that it has to be between
the points (-14,114) and (14,86). Otherwise it could happen that the border
will be destroyed.

@{bg shine}FillColor...@{bg background}

Sets the fillcolor for the minuteelement.

@{bg shine}BorderColor...@{bg background}

Sets the bordercolor for the minute-element.

@{bg shine}Shadow@{bg background}

Switchs the shadow on/off.

@{bg shine}Shadow Depth...@{bg background}

Sets the shadowdepth for the minute-element.
@ENDNODE

