@NODE "background" "Background"

Settings for @{u}@{b}background@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}Open...@{bg background}

Loads a brush as a background.
From OS 2.1 MagicClock uses Datatypes to load.
Otherwise the @{"iff.library" link "ifflib"} was used.

@{bg shine}Remap@{bg background}

If Remap is turned on the colors of the loaded picture will fitted
to the workbenchcolors (only Datatypes).

@{bg shine}Scale Picture To Windowsize@{bg background}

Scales the loaded picture to windowsize.
Also after expanding or reducing the windowsize.

@{bg shine}Brush@{bg background}

Used a picture as background for the clock.
If you haven't chosen a picture before, a filerequester will opened.
(won't saved in the unregistred version)

@{bg shine}Snap@{bg background}

Snaps the graphics behind the window.
(won't saved in the unregistred version)

@{bg shine}Snap Always@{bg background}

It does the same as Snap, but it will do it always after moving and sizing
the window and also when the background was changed.
(won't saved in the unregistred version)

@{bg shine}Empty@{bg background}

Sets the background to a simple color.

@{bg shine}Pattern@{bg background}

Puts a colorpattern into the background.

@{bg shine}Dithering@{bg background}
(won't saved in the unregistred version)

Puts a nice colorbleed into the window.

@{bg shine}Snap Delay@{bg background}

That means the time before the program snaps the background.
Thats important, if you want to snap a simple-refresh-window that needs
longer for refreshing.
It's the same for Snap and SnapMode.

@{bg shine}Notification@{bg background}

Watches the workbench background and snaps the new backgound after a 3 sec.
delay.
This functions is only available by using >Snap Always<.

@{bg shine}Empty Color@{bg background}

Sets the color for the one-colored background.

@{bg shine}Pattern Color 1@{bg background}

Sets color 1 (above right) for the colorpattern.

@{bg shine}Pattern Color 2@{bg background}

Sets color 2 (above left) for the colorpattern.

@{bg shine}Pattern Color 3@{bg background}

Sets color 3 (below right) for the colorpattern.

@{bg shine}Pattern Color 4@{bg background}

Sets color 4 (below left) for the colorpattern.

@{"Dithermode" link "dithermode"}

Special settings for dithering.

@{bg shine}Dither Color 1@{bg background}

Sets color 1 (above) for the the dithering.

@{bg shine}Dither Color 2@{bg background}

Sets color 2 (centre/below) for the dithering.

@{bg shine}Dither Color 3@{bg background}

Sets color 3 (below) for the dithering.
@ENDNODE

@node "dithermode" "Dithermode"

@{bg shine}Three Color Dithering@{bg background}

Switchs between 2 or 3 colors for the dithering.

@{bg shine}Ordered@{bg background}

Switchs to Ordered-Dithering.

@{bg shine}Dot@{bg background}

Switchs to Dotmatrix-Dithering.
@endnode

@NODE "border" "Border"

Settings for the @{b}@{u}windowborder@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}No Border@{bg background}

Draws no border around the window.

@{bg shine}Single Border@{bg background}

Draws a simple border around the window. Settings for outer border were used.

@{bg shine}Double Border@{bg background}

Draws a double border with the user settings around the window.

@{bg shine}Transparent@{bg background}

Puts the brush also into the border.
If Transparent is inactivated a special fillcolor will be used.

@{bg shine}Borderwidth@{bg background}

Sets the horizontal width of the doubleborder.

@{bg shine}Borderheight@{bg background}

Sets the vertical width of the doubleborder.

@{"  Activated  " link "activated"}  Adjustments for the activated window
@{" Inactivated " link "inactivated"}  Adjustments for the inactivated window

@ENDNODE

@NODE "activated" "Activated"

Settings for the @{u}@{b}activated window@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}Shine Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "bright" side of the outer border.

@{bg shine}Shadow Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "dark" side of the outer border.

@{bg shine}Inner Shine Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "bright" side of the border.

@{bg shine}Inner Shadow Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "dark" side of the border.

@{bg shine}FillColor...@{bg background}

Sets the fillcolor of the border. (Transparents has to be turned off)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "inactivated" "Inactivated"

Settings for the @{u}@{b}inactivated window@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}Shine Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "bright" side of the outer border.

@{bg shine}Shadow Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "dark" side of the outer border.

@{bg shine}Inner Shine Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "bright" side of the border.

@{bg shine}Inner Shadow Color...@{bg background}

Sets the color for the "dark" side of the border.

@{bg shine}FillColor...@{bg background}

Sets the fillcolor of the border. (Transparents has to be turned off)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "sound" "Sound"

Settings for @{u}@{b}sound output@{ub}@{uu}

@{"  Alarm   " link "alarm"}  Special adjustments for Alarmoutput
@{"  Counter " link "counter"}  Special adjustments for counter
@{"  Chime   " link "chime"}
@{"  Hour    " link "sethour"} 
@{"  Quarter " link "setquarter"}
@{"  Half    " link "sethalf"}

@{bg shine}Set Play Buffer...@{bg background}

Sets how many memory will be allocated as buffer for playing samples.

@{bg shine}Stop Sound@{bg background}

Stops the current playing sound.

@{bg shine}Stop At Activation@{bg background}

If this switch is on, every playing sound will be stopped by activating the
window.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "alarm" "Alarm"

@{u}@{b}Alarmsettings@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}On/Off@{bg background}

Turns the alarm on/off.

@{bg shine}Set Alarm...@{bg background}

Sets the alarmtime.

@{bg shine}Open Sample...@{bg background}

Opens a sample that plays on alarmtime.
It only supports uncrunched mono IFF samples, up to 28000 Hz.
The menuitem beep has to be turned off.

@{bg shine}Beep@{bg background}

Switchs to beep.

@{bg shine}Sample@{bg background}

Activates the samplemode.

@{bg shine}Sound Options...@{bg background}

Includes some settings for the activated mode.

@{i}Sample:@{ui}

        - only volume

@{i}beep:@{ui}

        - @{bg fill}Frequency@{bg background}    - Play frequency
        - @{bg fill}Volume@{bg background}       - Play volume
        - @{bg fill}Beep Length@{bg background}
        - @{bg fill}Delay@{bg background}        - How much time it takes until the beep restarts

@{bg fill}Okay@{bg background}            -       Uses settings
@{bg fill}Test@{bg background}            -       Tests settings
@{bg fill}Stop@{bg background}            -       Stops testing
@{bg fill}Closebutton@{bg background}     -       Settings will be lost

@{bg shine}Set Play Buffer...@{bg background}

Sets how much memory for buffering the program gets for playing sample.

@{bg shine}Set Count...@{bg background}

Sets how often the sample or the beep will be played.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "counter" "Counter"

@{u}@{b}Countersettings@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg shine}On/Off@{bg background}

Turns the counter on/off.

@{bg shine}Set Alarm...@{bg background}

Sets the counter time.

@{bg shine}Open Sample...@{bg background}

Opens a sample that plays on alarmtime.
It only supports uncrunched mono IFF samples, up to 28000 Hz.
The menuitem beep has to be turned off.

@{bg shine}Beep@{bg background}

Switchs to beep.

@{bg shine}Sample@{bg background}

Acivates the samplemode.

@{bg shine}Sound Options...@{bg background}

Includes some settings for the activated mode.

@{i}Sample:@{ui}

        - only volume

@{i}Beep:@{ui}

        - @{bg fill}Frequency@{bg background}    - Play frequency
        - @{bg fill}Volume@{bg background}       - Play volume
        - @{bg fill}Beep Length@{bg background}
        - @{bg fill}Delay@{bg background}        - How much time it takes until the beep restarts

@{bg fill}Okay@{bg background}            -       Uses settings
@{bg fill}Test@{bg background}            -       Tests settings
@{bg fill}Stop@{bg background}            -       Stops testing
@{bg fill}Closebutton@{bg background}     -       Settings will be lost

@{bg shine}Set Count...@{bg background}

Sets how often the sample or the beep will be played.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "chime" "Chime"

A signal will be played:

  @{bg shine}None@{bg background}    - never
  @{bg shine}Hour@{bg background}    - hourly
  @{bg shine}Half@{bg background}    - every half hour
  @{bg shine}Quarter@{bg background} - every quarter of an hour

@ENDNODE


@NODE "sethour" "Hour"

